Package: caladaptR
Title: Access Cal-Adapt Climate Data from R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Akash", "B V",
           email = "abv1@bu.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("David", "LeBauer",
           email = "dlebauer@gmail.com",
           role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7228-053X"))
    )
Description: Provides native R access to the Cal-Adapt Analytics Engine,
    California's repository of downscaled CMIP6 climate projections.
    Supports both WRF dynamically downscaled (hourly, 3/9/45 km) and
    LOCA2-Hybrid statistically downscaled (daily, 3 km) datasets.
    Reads cloud-optimized Zarr stores directly from AWS S3 via GDAL,
    with no Python dependency.
